wiiwhiteboard python implementation

*** REQUIRED PACKAGES ***

This little software works under linux and Windows.

---------------------LINUX-------------------
It requires the following packages:

libbluez2
bluez-firmware
bluez-pin
bluez-utils
python >=2.4
pybluez (also called python-bluetooth)
python-xlib
wxpython (for the gtk interface)

* RUNNING *
From the shell, simply type: 
	
	python gtkwhiteboard.py

-----------------WINDOWS------------------------
The following must be installed:

.NET Framework
python >=2.4 **
wxpython **

** Not required to run from binary

* RUNNING *
Start by connecting the wiimote with your bluetooth device manager (bluesoleil or something alike)
Then, double-click on the gtkwhiteboard.py file or gtkwhiteboard.exe (if running from binary file)


*** TROUBLESHOOTING *** 
If you get errors messages under Linux about the program not being able to access the 
bluetooth device, make sure bluez-utils is installed and that the bluetooth
service is running (/etc/init.d/bluetooth restart)

